18:47.017 --> 18:54.465
Yeah, so for people that say, why don't we do X instead of focusing so much on Y?

18:54.506 --> 19:03.576
It's like, well, first of all, we do X and Y, because the Bible tells us in Judea and Samaria and in the outermost parts of the world.

19:03.596 --> 19:08.562
So we're supposed to start where we are in our city and then expand out from there.

19:08.834 --> 19:33.106
But I think it goes back to the quote that I use about the log, that great imbalance video that we saw, like there is something about, like my wife and I were talking about it on our drive home yesterday, because we're just comparing it to Joy's experience in Iran and talking about the hairdresser story, how this woman been praying for five years for the opportunity to meet another Christian.

19:33.250 --> 19:33.991
Yeah.

19:34.432 --> 19:35.874
We can't even wrap our minds around that.

19:35.894 --> 19:40.781
I mean, the fact I drive from Tinley Park to Manhattan, where I live, it's a 30-minute drive.

19:41.302 --> 19:48.653
In that 30-minute drive, I, without exaggeration, two dozen, three dozen, four dozen churches all pass on that drive.

19:48.753 --> 19:53.300
I'm passing plenty of opportunity to meet other Christians.

19:53.360 --> 20:00.210
So when you live in the US and you are not a believer, it's by choice.

20:00.418 --> 20:06.028
When you live in some of the countries that we work in and you're not a believer, a lot of times it's not by choice, it's by ignorance.

20:06.048 --> 20:14.522
Literally, we talk with people who have never heard the name Jesus before, which sounds so crazy because we're surrounded by it.

20:14.923 --> 20:17.948
And it sounds crazy because it's like, well, doesn't the internet, don't they have the internet?

20:18.069 --> 20:20.533
And some of these places, well, no, they don't.

20:20.853 --> 20:25.842
And even places that do, it's not part of culture, it's not part of what's around them.

20:25.922 --> 20:30.669
And so even if they know something, they don't know much, like even Joyce testimony.

20:30.889 --> 20:36.717
She's like, I didn't really know Jesus, even though in Islam, we recognize Jesus as a prophet.

20:36.737 --> 20:43.947
So we knew stuff about Jesus, but she was like, but then all of a sudden I start reading the Bible and I realized like the stuff that we had been told about Jesus is not true.

20:43.967 --> 20:54.482
And so like we want to target, we want to go to places where the opportunity to hear the gospel is just not present.

20:55.138 --> 21:10.738
stood out to me in her testimony was all of the we're gonna just call it what it was the supernatural encounters she had with the Holy Spirit and it just made me wonder if

21:11.170 --> 21:15.455
that needed to be done for her to establish a relationship with Jesus.

21:15.555 --> 21:21.882
It was kind of like, we don't hear a lot of that here in the United States, but her coming to Christ was very supernatural.

21:21.942 --> 21:22.823
So I don't know, was it?

21:22.843 --> 21:24.404
Man, were you in the car with us yesterday?

21:24.444 --> 21:26.547
Like we were having that same exact conversation.

21:26.567 --> 21:26.987
I was not, but yeah.

21:27.107 --> 21:29.350
Because we were talking about the difference between need and want.

21:29.430 --> 21:30.331
Yeah.

21:30.351 --> 21:40.622
And we basically talked through, because she mentioned that whole like, why do Iranians have so many dreams about Jesus and meet him in a dream?

21:40.662 --> 21:40.882
Yeah.

21:41.026 --> 21:45.219
And yet, like Americans are like, I would love to see Jesus have a dream.

21:46.182 --> 21:49.030
And it's the difference between a need and a want.

21:49.131 --> 21:51.538
Like, without that dream,

21:51.618 --> 21:55.444
For an Iranian, the chances of them coming to faith in Christ is very, very low.

21:56.245 --> 22:02.435
They need that moment because they're living in a place where there is no billboard that says, God Jesus.

22:04.558 --> 22:06.762
Isn't that one that's here in Chicago?

22:06.842 --> 22:08.004
You're not going to see it.

22:08.405 --> 22:11.890
And so Jesus visiting in a dream, it's a necessity.

22:12.034 --> 22:14.557
Whereas for us, we'd be like, wouldn't that be so neat?

22:15.218 --> 22:16.200
Like, wouldn't it be so cool?

22:16.280 --> 22:17.982
I want to write a book about it.

22:18.002 --> 22:23.950
And then even for non-believers in the US that would say, yeah, but if Jesus showed up to me in a dream, then I would believe.

22:24.211 --> 22:29.498
And it's like, the Bible actually even says, blessed are those who believe without seeing.

22:29.518 --> 22:29.618
Yeah.

22:29.638 --> 22:29.838
Right?

22:29.958 --> 22:35.766
And so, like, I think that there is a faith component to this, but there's a need versus want.

22:36.447 --> 22:41.394
One thing that's really interesting, and I wish we had time to really dig into it with her,

22:41.634 --> 22:57.467
But Elon, one of the things that they do is they train up Iranians in Turkey, and I think I'm safe in saying some of this, because Turkey and Iran have a very easy relationship.

22:57.568 --> 23:02.578
Turkey is open to Christianity and things because it's a tourist-built nation.

23:02.722 --> 23:06.406
And they know that if they strike down on Christianity, then they lose their tourism.

23:07.087 --> 23:10.191
So Turkey is very like, hey, we're staying out of this one, guys.

23:11.272 --> 23:15.077
But that becomes a vacation destination for Iranians.

23:15.097 --> 23:19.142
So they can come in to Turkey for like three months.

23:19.422 --> 23:22.186
It's like a three month visa that's easy to get.

23:23.007 --> 23:25.009
It's basically there's like practically no restriction.

23:25.450 --> 23:29.074
So what they do is they set up a 90 day Bible schools.

23:29.314 --> 23:31.117
And so they do like crash course.

23:32.259 --> 23:34.121
And it's all day, every day.

23:34.282 --> 23:36.365
Like it's not like a couple of hours here.

23:36.405 --> 23:39.410
No, it's like it's intensive, three month program.

23:39.790 --> 23:44.237
You get trained to be a pastor, then you go back into Iran as an underground church pastor.

23:44.958 --> 23:50.026
And so when I was in Turkey, I got to go and visit the building where they're housing this in.

23:50.807 --> 23:52.570
And there was about a dozen people there.

23:53.531 --> 23:57.938
Of the dozen, I would say eight of them had a dream of Jesus.

23:58.114 --> 23:59.416
before they became Christian.

24:02.219 --> 24:08.267
The four that didn't have a dream still had some kind of like supernatural component to it.

24:08.467 --> 24:18.219
It was like, I was having a really bad day and I'm in a taxi and all of a sudden the taxi driver is like, hey, are you okay?

24:18.239 --> 24:19.101
Can I pray for you?

24:19.181 --> 24:22.365
Which is like, that's not like here in the US.

24:22.385 --> 24:23.386
You knew that no problem.

24:23.406 --> 24:26.610
But like, that was a huge risk for the driver to say that.

24:26.786 --> 24:44.998
Another one it was like a fairly similar story on a subway or on a bus or something But the eight that had a dream like it was just it was amazing hearing their stories hearing the testimony because we just asked all 12 of them just tell us how they became Christian because That's it's a powerful story every time you ask.

24:45.098 --> 24:49.906
Yeah, it's not well, you know my parents were Christian and I was born into it or I was

24:49.986 --> 24:51.849
raised by it, or I was having a really hard time.

24:51.869 --> 24:54.393
So I went to my local church and I found Jesus there.

24:54.413 --> 24:56.936
And like, that's not the testimonies of Iranians.

24:57.056 --> 25:02.264
It's, man, it's, it's, there's so much supernatural in the part of it, which is really cool to see.

25:02.344 --> 25:02.665
Yeah.

25:02.925 --> 25:04.367
No, that was awesome to hear.

25:05.188 --> 25:10.356
But Pastor Aceo, what, I know you go on mission trips.

25:10.576 --> 25:13.421
That's something you encourage all your leaders to do here, Pastor Brent.

25:13.801 --> 25:17.106
But do you feel like there was a moment where you felt like,

25:18.562 --> 25:23.329
Can you say you can be called to a mission trip or is it just like you should just go?

25:24.851 --> 25:28.756
Being called to a specific trip or any trip or missions in general?

25:28.856 --> 25:32.041
Is mission something you feel like you are called to?

25:32.061 --> 25:34.164
I mean, I feel like I've heard that.

25:34.244 --> 25:37.028
I just feel like I wanted to be a missionary.

25:37.048 --> 25:38.510
I was calling me to do that.

25:38.850 --> 25:44.338
So for myself, when I was in Bible school,

25:44.546 --> 25:47.772
My wife was wanting to know, why are you in Bible school?

25:47.972 --> 25:49.334
And I'm like, I don't know.

25:49.494 --> 25:51.879
I feel like I'm in Bible school, because God told me to go.

25:51.959 --> 25:53.000
So I'm in Bible school.

25:53.702 --> 25:55.124
And she would say, do you want to be a pastor?

25:55.144 --> 25:55.765
Do you want to be this?

25:55.805 --> 25:57.228
And I'm like, Tracy, I don't, I don't know.

25:57.248 --> 25:59.652
No, I was like, no, I really don't want to be a pastor.

25:59.672 --> 26:02.316
That's the thing I know I don't want to be is a pastor.

26:02.336 --> 26:03.358
I'm taking one step.

26:03.378 --> 26:05.542
I'm asking me about 20 minutes.

26:05.562 --> 26:06.463
She needed the rest.

26:06.524 --> 26:07.726
I didn't need it.

26:07.746 --> 26:10.290
And literally the only answer I could give her

26:10.562 --> 26:11.704
I would always land on.

26:12.024 --> 26:21.479
The only thing I could see myself doing, and then I would give the caveat, but you're not gonna do this is I would love to just go do missions and be in the middle of nowhere doing missions.

26:21.839 --> 26:23.101
And she's like, yeah, we're not doing that.

26:23.141 --> 26:25.024
So I don't have you there for that.

26:25.405 --> 26:29.171
That's the only thing I could land on that actually like, that sounds cool.

26:29.191 --> 26:30.553
And I don't even know where that came from.

26:31.274 --> 26:39.026
If I think about it, I guess I grew up in a church where there was a lot of African missions going on at least

26:39.746 --> 26:41.388
I didn't necessarily see people going.

26:41.428 --> 26:42.710
I know we sent a lot of money there.

26:43.611 --> 26:47.656
So I probably gave as a kid toward missions to Africa and different things like that.

26:48.477 --> 26:51.100
So I don't know where that seed was planted in me to like missions.

26:51.260 --> 26:53.603
But that was the only thing I could come up with.

26:53.623 --> 26:54.804
Like missions sound good.

26:54.864 --> 26:58.308
I'd be glad to go live somewhere and do missions.

26:58.328 --> 26:59.490
And Tracy was like, no.

27:00.191 --> 27:03.014
So from that standpoint, something in me likes missions.

27:03.114 --> 27:03.915
I will say that.

27:03.975 --> 27:07.079
And I didn't just come up with that.

27:07.600 --> 27:09.682
But when it comes to like specific trips,

27:10.370 --> 27:14.317
Yeah, God can surely call you to a specific trip or call you to missions in general.

27:14.337 --> 27:15.478
How it happened for me?

27:15.599 --> 27:18.944
I signed up for the Panama trip, which was supposed to happen in 2020.

27:19.665 --> 27:20.527
Got canceled.

27:20.887 --> 27:22.911
I don't remember why I signed up for that trip.

27:22.951 --> 27:23.552
I don't even know.

27:23.692 --> 27:24.794
It might have just been timing.

27:25.175 --> 27:25.876
Signed up for it.

27:25.976 --> 27:28.460
That was supposed to be Jaden's first missions experience.

27:28.480 --> 27:28.761
Okay.

27:29.001 --> 27:29.281
Yeah.

27:29.462 --> 27:29.702
Yeah.

27:30.283 --> 27:32.286
And it was postponed or it was canceled.

27:32.327 --> 27:34.450
So when we start going on mission trips again,

27:34.626 --> 27:36.968
I literally was like, well, I don't already raised this money.

27:37.028 --> 27:37.869
I need to go somewhere.

27:37.909 --> 27:40.752
And the next trip that was up, that worked on the schedule was the Philippines.

27:41.152 --> 27:43.455
So the guy called me to go to the Philippines.

27:44.195 --> 27:45.517
Yeah, I can't tell you that.

27:45.657 --> 27:48.820
I just went because that was the next trip on the docket.

27:48.840 --> 27:50.862
But something in me does, like missions.

27:50.882 --> 27:54.705
And then Japan, I was told I was going to Japan.

27:55.286 --> 27:56.607
So yeah, so that's kind of.

27:56.627 --> 27:58.289
I wonder who told you.

27:58.309 --> 28:03.634
But both of them, I would say, have been super impactful in my life.

28:03.970 --> 28:06.735
I feel like I hopefully impacted people where I was at.

28:07.436 --> 28:10.121
So it was good in both ways.

28:10.802 --> 28:11.824
Yeah, I think there's room for both.

28:11.884 --> 28:19.398
I think there's a space of just pure obedience of like, look, God told me to go because he told all of us to go.

28:19.418 --> 28:21.101
And so I'm going to go.

28:21.161 --> 28:23.986
And my church is offering these six options.

28:24.407 --> 28:25.970
And of the six, that one sounds cool.

28:26.431 --> 28:27.072
Never been there.

28:27.092 --> 28:28.274
I wanted to go there.

28:28.546 --> 28:38.697
We try not to treat missions as a vacation, but the number of people that go on a trip simply because they really want to be in that country is pretty high.

28:38.917 --> 28:40.879
And I don't think that's necessarily a bad thing.

28:40.899 --> 28:46.225
Now, if you neglect the work so you can take pictures and be a tourist, like, okay, that's not okay.

28:47.406 --> 28:49.728
But if you're like, man, I've never been to Japan before.

28:49.748 --> 28:51.831
I love Japanese culture.

28:51.851 --> 28:54.994
I love sushi and anime.

28:55.490 --> 28:56.893
Don't on the Japan trip, why not?

28:56.914 --> 28:59.761
I get a lot of that with Japan.

28:59.821 --> 29:02.106
A lot of people are like, I just always wanted to go to Japan.

29:02.267 --> 29:05.555
I love all of those things you said.

29:05.595 --> 29:11.730
I'll be honest, when we first connected with Pastor Fabio and they're like, we're going to do a Japan trip.

29:11.970 --> 29:13.211
Dibs.

29:15.094 --> 29:17.937
I get to be the guy to lead that one the first time out.

29:18.037 --> 29:21.841
First of all, it's a first time trip, which means you never know what's going to happen.

29:22.742 --> 29:26.627
But my son loved Japanese stuff and I love Japanese stuff.

29:26.667 --> 29:29.410
And it was like, this will be a cool father-son moment.

29:29.430 --> 29:31.232
So I was like, all right, I'm leading Japan.

29:31.372 --> 29:32.233
Jaden, you're coming with.

29:32.253 --> 29:32.613
Let's go.

29:33.254 --> 29:33.875
I love that.

29:34.015 --> 29:36.638
I mean, that's a spoil.

29:36.838 --> 29:40.242
Any of the things coming up for the next week, but it does highlight

29:40.322 --> 29:58.002
going on mission trips with your kids like that's one of the videos we're gonna highlight but I love that I know there's a trip I'm eyeing right now from this Sunday and we're gonna unpack those trips in this episode I can't wait to hear what Taisha's gonna go next year already there's two places one I have to go to

29:58.434 --> 30:02.162
You can probably get one that I want to go through with my family.

30:02.182 --> 30:02.703
Can you guys?

